    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="775"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 25, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Army is now assisting in policing city. General Blanche has been made
                    Commander in Chief and we are practically under martial law. Serious clashes are
                    feared about midday when crowds return from funeral of doctor killed yesterday.
                    Public feeling against Ibaüez bitter. Doctors, lawyers, and engineers have gone
                    on a strike and have adopted resolutions asking him to resign and further
                    strikes are likely. Business is at a standstill.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
